President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key administration posts: Joan Evans for Assistant Secretary for Congressional and Legislative Affairs at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Warren F. "Pete" Miller, Jr., PhD for Assistant Secretary for Nuclear Energy at the Department of Energy, and John R. Norris for Commissioner at the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Joan Evans has previously served as Chief of Staff to Congresswoman Darlene Hooley, while Warren F. "Pete" Miller, Jr., PhD has worked as a professor at Texas A&M University and at Los Alamos National Laboratory. John R. Norris currently serves as Chief of Staff for Secretary Tom Vilsack at the U.S. Department of Agriculture and has also held positions in the Iowa Utilities Board and the National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners.